sql:
SELECT patient_id
FROM patients
WHERE patient_id NOT IN (SELECT patient_id FROM patient_preferences);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM patient_lens_outcomes 
WHERE outcome = 'Fair';

external_knowledge:
- 'Hyperope' refers to farsightedness, a condition where distant objects can be seen more clearly than near objects; 
- 'Yes' for astigmatism indicates the presence of this eye condition characterized by blurred vision due to an irregularly shaped cornea; 
- 'Reduced' tear production rate signifies below normal tear production in the eyes.
